            <div class="mtext">
  <div class="title">
    The State Company 'Ukrspecexport' has taken part in the 7th International Air Show 'Aviasvit- XXI'
  </div>
  <div class="news-line"></div>
  <div class="tbody">
  <p> The 7th International Air Show 'Aviasvit – XXІ' was opened in Gostomel, Kyiv region, on September  30, 2010. More than 280 enterprises and companies of the aerospace industry from 32 countries had the opportunity to participate actively in the air show.</p>

 

         <p>Volodymyr Lytvyn, the current Chairman of the Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine (the Ukrainian Parliament), Dmytro Koliesnikov, the Minister of Industrial Policy of Ukraine, as well as the People's Deputies of Ukraine, the Heads of leading Ukraine's aerospace and missile building enterprises participated in the Air Show Grand Opening. </p>

        <p> Volodymyr Lytvyn - on behalf of the President of Ukraine and the Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine – delivered his address to the exhibitors and public visitors of the Air Show and thanked the builders of the aircrafts (aviation equipment) personally for their major contribution made to the economic prosperity of our society, as well as to the uniting of countries and nations. "The Air Sow strikingly illustrates that it is necessary to join and concentrate our efforts to promote the welfare of mankind", said the Chairman of the Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine.     </p>

        <p> Bidding a ceremonial welcome to the exhibitors and public visitors of the Air Show – on behalf of the Government of Ukraine and Mykolo Azarov, the Prime Minister of Ukraine - Dmytro Koliesnikov, the Minister of Industrial Policy of Ukraine, wished in his turn the exhibiting enterprises a good luck and success in entering into new profitable contracts.    
       The State Company 'Ukrspecexport' traditionally attended the air show. 'Anatra', the model of biplane reconstructed by 'Odessa Aircraft Repair Plant 'Odesaviaremservice', was a peculiarity of the Company's stand. During the air show Mykhailo Yezhel, the Minister of Defence of Ukraine, as well as the official delegations and representatives of various foreign countries, including the Russian Federation, Kuwait and Saudi Arabia, visited the stand of the SC 'Ukrspecexport'. </p>

        <p>The aircrafts demonstration flights have become the most impressive event in the air show programme. The exhibitors and public visitors of the 'Aviasvit' air show could watch the following:<br />
&bull;&nbsp;demonstration flights of An-225, 'Mriya', An-148, An-158 and An-74, cargo aircrafts;<br />
&bull;&nbsp;solo flying of Su-30MKI, fighter aircraft;<br />
&bull;&nbsp;flying of four L-39, training aircrafts;<br />
&bull;&nbsp;solo and formation flying of helicopters, light sport aircrafts  and biplanes. </p>
        <div style="margin-top: 5px; margin-bottom: 5px;"><a href="/index/viewphoto/lang/eng/p/aviasvit">Photoreport »</a>
